reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Rodolfo Arouca', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111544286639190345926/reviews', 'language': 'pt', 'original_language': 'pt', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWsRxQz7_0tR11hyqcBkdsNwYniq6f-r0J0WA33h5AecxhBi_LR=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a week ago', 'text': 'Já pensou entrar em um ambiente aconchegante e encontrar um bar de vinhos onde a Proprietaria (Analu Torres) apresenta mais de 18 rótulos em taça de cabeça? Contando um pouco de cada um sem ler de um cardápio e ainda falando cada preço (ideia ótima que evita qualquer tipo de constrangimento de vc querer pedir um vinho pq gostou da descrição e descobre que custa 120 reais a taça) - aliás é nítida a preocupação com diferentes faixas de preço, começando com valores tão baixos quanto 38 reais pra taça e garrafas com bom custo benefício. Várias opções de vinhos franceses, mas também espanholas, croatas e etc. Analu e demais pessoas que estavam trabalhando lá todas com uma paixão incrível por vinho e fazendo tudo para que a nossa experiência fosse ótima.

Quem melhor do que pessoas apaixonadas de vinho para indicar vinhos, né?

O cardápio de comidas é enxuto, mas opções perfeitas para beliscar ou até comer enquanto aprecia-se os vinhos. Preços também justos, tábua de queijos e de charcuterie deliciosas com valores de 38 e 44 reais respectivamente. Não são grandes, mas essas duas serviram bem 3 pessoas.

Poderia dizer que existem “4” ambientes, por mais que não haja uma grande ruptura entre eles. A área de fora antes de entrar, que imagino que num dia de muito movimento vc possa sentar em uma cadeirinha de praia ou ficar de pé, o salão principal com opções de cadeira com mesa e até um sofazinho, o bar em si com cerca de 8 lugares, e um corredor lateral externo com bancadas altas pra degustar um vinho em pé enquanto joga conversa fora.

A playlist estava ótima, músicas variadas principalmente anos 80-90. Volume ideal pra quebrar o silêncio intimidador, mas sem atrapalhar a conversa.

Todo o cuidado na curadoria das peças de decoração e no design também aparece. O logo é um charme por si só.

Existem várias opções de bares de vinho em São Paulo, mas o Plou me surpreendeu pelo atendimento, qualidade e custo benefício. Tem tudo pra ser meu favorito, preciso voltar mais vezes pra tirar a prova.', 'time': 1731767216, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Jacomo Piccolini', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101673922892549246764/reviews', 'language': 'pt', 'original_language': 'pt', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCST6gewQIi9NYEHBjkN57EqL1v4JRAq2eevXWcqLO8q2ih25akw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': 'Plou Vinhos Naturais, o melhor ambiente para uma taça ou garrafa de vinhos naturais e um acompanhamento pra beliscar! Analu com um conhecimento único sobre vinhos! Equipe super competente e sensacional!', 'time': 1723775480, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Daniela Christine', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101967049458609181531/reviews', 'language': 'pt', 'original_language': 'pt', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUZZF7QzGIf27T8-Qggj1Bd-l-wgVNDC1blioI5HVn4vcDBzp9y=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': 'Fui conhecer o novo espaço mas estava sendo realizado um evento de degustação de vinhos e ainda não tinham as porções e pratos, portanto não deu para avaliar. Vou voltar posteriormente para experimentar. A princípio adianto que amei o local. Bem descontraído mas com uma decoração de muito bom gosto, o espaço não é muito grande mas é aconchegante e ainda tem um banco e aparadores na calçada (onde fiquei pois o dia estava quente e estava bem cheio mas curti mesmo assim).', 'time': 1724016823, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Bruno Szczypkovski', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115652807623655183953/reviews', 'language': 'pt', 'original_language': 'pt', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK1Ny2ICF7OBhZ0GB5S2HaRhiJJqBtBM30e6z52iXuFIz191JA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'Lugar lindo, aconchegante e com uma carta de vinhos invejável. Certamente é mais uma coluna importante para a evolução do mercado do bom vinho no Brasil. Parabéns pela coragem e pela dedicação.', 'time': 1727902103, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Mike Zambotto', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117002067422808541642/reviews', 'language': 'pt', 'original_language': 'pt', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWXg1wqcUo_V-A4L72oPUbfQXBqlEkxSYST2E18OyS_GlyZjHyC=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'Percebi um tratamento bem desdenhado pela tal da Analu pelo simples fato de eu ter dito que gosto de Chardonnay. Entendo que vinho bom é aquele que te agrada, independentemente de origem, preço, uva.', 'time': 1726187338, 'translated': False}]

Overall, it was a good experience.', 'time': 1716627272, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Alireza Shirazi', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110819921470495938421/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWMPPs2kuR7kwfJBi1TQUtAVr0F-9J2EnaM1DjZEX3IUXmFTg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': "Returning to Nabucco after 20 years, since I fell in love with their Ossobuco dish all those years ago.
Naturally, I made a reservation for my first night back in Milan, eager to revisit the flavors that once captivated me.
Unfortunately, while the wine selection has impressively maintained its quality over the decades, the same can't be said for the food. I tried a range of dishes, including Parmigiana di melanzane, Zucchine alla scapece, Tagliolino al tartufo nero estivo, and, of course, the iconic Risotto allo zafferano e ossobuco. Sadly, the quality of the dishes didn't live up to my memories.
It was disappointing to see such a decline in the standard of the cuisine, especially from a place I once held in such high regard.", 'time': 1726332009, 'translated': False}]

The prices were reasonable, with plenty of good choices..', 'time': 1719578336, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Sam Aberman', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111941996399252793572/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWW8LD98tdvZGX2GSpZHvoTTtCKd8qb17YM2nQsTU6mmb_xz9uN7Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba8', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': "I recently visited the Wembley Designer Outlet on a sunny weekday and was pleasantly surprised by the open layout, which made for an enjoyable shopping experience. The clean and well-maintained premises added to the overall appeal.

One of the highlights of the outlet is the good selection of restaurants, offering a variety of cuisines to suit different tastes. This makes it easy to take a break from shopping and grab a bite to eat.

However, I would advise against visiting on weekends, as it can get extremely busy, making it difficult to navigate the shops and find what you're looking for. The crowds can be overwhelming, detracting from the overall experience.

While the outlet boasts a range of stores, I couldn't help but notice that there was an overabundance of shoe shops and not enough variety in terms of fashion. This might be disappointing for those seeking a more diverse shopping experience.

That being said, with a bit of patience and persistence, there are indeed bargains to be found. Many shops offer discounted prices on popular brands, making it worth the effort to hunt for good deals.

In summary, the Wembley Designer Outlet is a decent shopping destination, particularly on a nice day when you can enjoy the open layout. Just be prepared for crowds on weekends and a somewhat limited fashion selection. If you're primarily looking for shoes or don't mind the lack of variety, you may find some great bargains here.", 'time': 1711646947, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Jeevith Narayanan', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117483816576684590117/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXURMVnJjsk4GV_uQvK2UJNl7fYViaGX8upNosp6U9rwN6DU3SP=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '4 months ago', 'text': 'I had an excellent experience at the London Designer Outlet! 🛍️ The variety of stores is impressive, featuring top brands at fantastic prices. All the stores had sales, making the already discounted prices even more attractive. 🤑

The shopping environment is clean, modern, and welcoming, making it a pleasure to browse and shop. 🏬 The food court offers a great selection of dining options, perfect for taking a break and refueling during a shopping spree. 🍔☕ The staff in the stores are friendly and helpful, providing excellent customer service. 😊 Additionally, the location is convenient, with ample parking and easy access to public transport. 🚗🚇

Overall, the London Designer Outlet is a must-visit for anyone looking to enjoy a day of shopping and dining at unbeatable prices. Highly recommend! 🌟', 'time': 1721773931, 'translated': False}]

He does everything, cleans tables, makes the sandwiches and yes, stops for wine breaks.

The time you are waiting the ambience is very strange. Dead quite. Everyone orders in silence. Everyone eats in silence. Everyone whispers to each other for the hour+ they are waiting.

reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Somm', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113776207906409607156/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9rTZ22GtrI_ak7w1U1bZ13DOjYAYoypY_3rs02gnjsiJiWrLdOQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '5 months ago', 'text': "Firstly, I don't usually give such detailed negative reviews unless a place is really not worth the time, experience, and money, which is the case here.

I know that it's owner-operated and they probably don't care about my review or that this review will affect their business at all, as they rely on tourists. There will always be people like us who find them on Google and decide to stop by.

Let me share my experience here.

We found this restaurant on Google Maps with a 4.7-star rating, which was above the overall ratings in the area. Considering it's a tourist area, 4.7 is pretty solid. So, we decided to have lunch here by walking in.

We arrived at 12:35, asking for a table for two. We were greeted by a lady with glasses at the coffee station who explained that they do two sittings. She asked if we wanted to sit in the first or second sitting. We wanted a quick lunch because we had plans and wanted to eat immediately, so we agreed to the first sitting. There were two big tables available at the time and one bar stool in front of the restaurant.

The lady said if we wanted to sit at the big table inside, there might be another couple sitting with us as it was a table for four, so we chose the bar stool outside. She also tell us the policy fjat you must order a minimum of two courses per person, so we would have to order four dishes to be able to eat there. We agreed because we didn't have time to look for another place.

We were seated and offered menus and a card written in Italian and English, stating the same thing the lady explained earlier. I posted a picture here. We ordered food not long after being seated: two antipasti—one with anchovy and potatoes and a mixed salumi board to share—and two plates of pasta.

Ten minutes passed and we received a basket of bread without olive oil and balsamic, but that was okay. They also dropped off the crostini (one small sauce bowl—that’s the amount they gave). Another ten minutes passed, and one of the waitresses came and said there would be a wait for the antipasti. She asked if we wanted to wait or if they could send the pasta now and serve the antipasti later when it was ready. We agreed to take the pasta now because we had to leave by 1:30 as our parking ticket time was ending.

Another ten minutes passed and they served our pasta as pictured. Filled pasta was served with sauce just chucked on top. The other pasta was completely overcooked. However, we didn’t want to say anything and tried to eat it. We almost finished the pasta dish and still didn’t receive our antipasti. It was now 1:10 pm. To slice the cured meat and put anchovies from the can on the plate, they managed to take more than 40 minutes.

At 1:15 pm, our anchovy dish arrived, full of oil and with cold potatoes. I was very upset and asked my partner to cancel the other dish as it was still not ready and we had to leave. But then it finally arrived—our mixed salumi dish. All the meat was old and dry like paper, as well as the toast on there. You can see it in the picture.

How ridiculous is it that they took 45 minutes to make dishes that require only plating?! We had to rush in 5 minutes to eat these as we had to run to the car park before we got fined. My partner went to pay and the owner offered us free coffee because he overheard my partner say to another tourist looking at the menu that it’s not worth it and to go somewhere else. (Yes! We we were at the front and told others that don’t come in that’s how we do not recommended that is)

reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Home Away From Home Ltd', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107801171528745144768/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIEPKArh5DYgR6_JIW8sYzhOs1xrkPKoYdYWji_e7uYvMz_uw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '4 months ago', 'text': 'The dinner experience here was much better than brunch - my review is for dinner. The food was high quality and full of flavour. I’d definitely recommend the pasta with scallop. The in house cocktails were really creative and excellent flavour and extremely well balanced (hello, no hangover). Very professional service. The set up is very pretty with a florist, extensive vase display and a selection of gifts you can buy.', 'time': 1720100774, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Emilian Haas', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103926755075239620621/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL4DHlbCwG_AJmErweiUdYk6d6pwtJcssGyqfPmgmTcgkXfkw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '5 months ago', 'text': 'Upon entering the restaurant, one is immediately struck by the unique decor and furnishings. In the entrance area, along with beautiful and unique decorative items available for purchase, there are cozy sofas and armchairs, as well as a flower shop where florists create artistic bouquets. Each room in this restaurant is decorated in a different style.

One room features a long, rectangular space with large, long wooden tables where one can enjoy a cozy candlelit dinner. The walls are sparsely plastered to reveal as much of the original brickwork as possible. Along one wall of this room, a large shelf displays colorful glass candle holders, arranged by color, creating a decorative highlight. Another room at the head of the restaurant boasts a glass roof; in the center stand a grand piano and a large bonsai tree.

In addition to its thoughtful and stylish decor, the restaurant excels with its outstanding service and exquisite food. The tasting menus are meticulously designed, with each course perfectly complementing the others. The same attention to detail found in the decor is reflected in the dishes. The service, led by Vittorio and Simona, is attentive and friendly, making us feel very welcome and comfortable.

La Menagere is definitely worth a visit—whether for a warm breakfast or a smoothie in the morning, a drink at the bar in the bistro at lunchtime, or a stylish dinner in the evening.', 'time': 1717187593, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'F S', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111561750879047440378/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI1NHbj3_D_OAAumkp1tLVigCGW10JVvifDefOBJOJ954Hbxw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'Very neat concept of a store with a cafe inside! Great location and fun atmosphere! Extensive menu with a wide variety of drinks and food. Only downside was the service. Both times we went the service was very reactive versus proactive. Nonetheless I would still return and spend more time here.', 'time': 1727608936, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Jennifer Manzo', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117695594093236632914/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKHBoIhquIL0enEc74aawmZ8vgLYg9JjQnfXcRf0rdi8AkBIQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': 'I was on the fence about visiting La Ménagère due to somewhat mixed reviews, but I’m so glad I did because I had such a great experience! We stopped in early for coffee and breakfast, which were very good. Service was attentive and kind, especially from those working behind the counter area toward the front. The space is breathtakingly beautiful and the shop sells such pretty, unique items. I ended up purchasing something for myself and a gift for my sister. Even if you don’t end up eating here, it’s worth popping in to shop and admire the beauty of the space. Definitely one of my favorite places in Florence!', 'time': 1714866691, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'BM', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110944339269465768555/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKhSpOh2lhVEgtdnlEFbJARw2tXH56cLurk5S_swpii_4mxX6n0g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'La Menagerie is overrated in my opinion.

While the ambiance is top-notch and definitely impressive, the food left much to be desired. The food itself was just okay, and it took far too long to be served. We ordered Avocado Toast, Eggs Benedict and Omelette.

To add to the disappointment, the coffee was never hot enough, which is frustrating.

Also, the food is quite expensive for the quality and service you get. I expected more, given the reputation and prices.', 'time': 1728645793, 'translated': False}]

Very recommended.', 'time': 1718078888, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Patrick Patrick', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107557588153745055831/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWI0RNmVckPRXmPZboJUEiRX2yPCMpgacCXgMNzgzSfFfg0Lf86uA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': "Mercato di Sant'Ambrogio

Mercato di Sant'Ambrogio is one of Florence's most authentic and beloved local markets. Here's why it's worth a visit:

Authentic Local Experience**: Unlike the more tourist-centric Mercato Centrale, Sant'Ambrogio offers a truly local experience. Many of the vendors cater to Florentines, giving the market a genuine, everyday atmosphere that feels less commercial and more traditional.

Fresh Produce**: The market is known for its fresh, locally sourced fruits, vegetables, meats, cheeses, and seafood. The quality of the produce is outstanding, and it’s a fantastic place to get a sense of Tuscany’s seasonal ingredients.

Artisan Products**: In addition to fresh food, the market has a variety of stalls offering artisanal products, such as olive oil, wines, pasta, and baked goods. There’s also a great selection of cured meats and cheeses, perfect for anyone wanting to try Tuscan specialties.

Street Food**: Mercato di Sant'Ambrogio is a great place to grab some authentic Tuscan street food. You can find panini, fresh pasta, and the famous lampredotto (a traditional Florentine tripe sandwich), all made fresh by vendors. It's a budget-friendly way to enjoy delicious local cuisine.

Indoor and Outdoor Sections**: The market is divided into indoor and outdoor sections. The outdoor part is full of fresh produce, flowers, and clothing stalls, while the indoor part houses butchers, fishmongers, and cheese vendors. The combination makes for a lively and varied shopping experience.

Local Eateries**: Some small trattorias and cafés surrounding the market are ideal for a quick meal or coffee. Many of these places serve dishes made from ingredients sourced directly from the market, ensuring freshness and flavor.

Atmosphere**: The market has a bustling yet relaxed vibe, with locals haggling over prices and vendors greeting regular customers. It’s an excellent spot for people-watching and soaking in the local culture of Florence.

Overall, Mercato di Sant'Ambrogio offers a genuine slice of Florentine life. Whether you're a foodie, a shopper, or just looking to experience everyday life in Florence, this market is a must-visit for its authenticity, quality products, and vibrant atmosphere.", 'time': 1727158817, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Chelsea Janes', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115861122069394249812/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhik_fpBfijXIJyMg9dy6_4OsjoZKzP-5o_16I0sgxK0MLNlfB=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '4 weeks ago', 'text': 'The market itself was actually much smaller than I'd anticipated, but it was still a nice stop for some local cheese, olives and bread. Florence looks beautiful in the morning sun beams☺️", 'time': 1717972488, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Swapnil Mahajan', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112247991073977586636/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXM7BMne8fXR5C8WoSDB0nNi5xN4tapciDfbx919BN9TZW1vF8wWg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '5 months ago', 'text': "The panoramic view of Florence is absolutely breathtaking and a must-see for anyone visiting the city. Whether you take in the vista from Piazzale Michelangelo, the top of the Duomo, or another vantage point, the sweeping views of Florence’s iconic skyline are unforgettable.

Piazzale Michelangelo offers an incredible, unobstructed view of the entire city, including the majestic Duomo, the Ponte Vecchio, and the rolling Tuscan hills in the distance. It’s an ideal spot for photography, especially at sunset when the city is bathed in a golden glow. The atmosphere is vibrant yet relaxed, with street vendors and musicians adding to the charm.

Climbing to the top of the Duomo is another fantastic way to experience Florence from above. The ascent is challenging but rewarding, providing close-up views of Brunelleschi's magnificent dome and panoramic scenes of the city below.

The view is best experienced with a leisurely visit, allowing time to take in the details of the cityscape and the surrounding countryside. The sight of the terracotta rooftops, historic buildings, and the Arno River winding through the city is truly captivating.

Overall, the panoramic view of Florence is an essential part of experiencing the city’s beauty and history. It’s a perfect blend of architectural splendor and natural scenery, offering a serene and inspiring perspective of this Renaissance gem. Highly recommended for anyone looking to capture the essence of Florence.", 'time': 1717315010, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Andy Mills', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118398800822278361934/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUoM3ideZrqfNhdqzYdN_cyyJeKAwoPREwOakiBjlfVzgA6YYM_=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'Fantastic views over looking Florence.

[{'author_name': 'James Topping', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101047541441292038098/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK351yiueDr1G3wdLaBjXiHiMiUxVlfd6DwMiZs91zxMmdLhw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'We arrived here before it opened at 11.55 and there were already 8 people waiting in line to get in. We waited until it opened by which time there were at least 25 people in the line.

They showed us to a to a table very fast and took our order. The wine and water came very fast and 5 minutes later the food arrived. We were done in 30 minutes. A fast and efficient service.

The food was delicious, the meatballs were very flavoursome as well as the cutlet.
The house wine was very well priced at €2.50 a glass or €4 for 250ml. Easy to drink.
Staff were friendly.

While we ate people continued to come in, but there was no wait.', 'time': 1725966682, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Quỳnh Lê', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100740520546737644828/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVpa-8mXbQk19byA7Cu1VL1vVnr2Zx-GBhU6OQN3GIWA9xGxnshow=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '4 months ago', 'text': 'The place is busy but I came during lunch so still able to get a table quite quickly. The price is affordable and the food was quite good. The salad was big. The pasta was really good, I really like it. The atmosphere gives you a local Italian restaurant vibe. Cozy and nice. The staffs are friendly and nice.', 'time': 1721860753, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Mustafa Omar', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108184493555182409058/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJW_Ubtz3n2CrPuQhSzp88IpyysET70bSad3w_CBB5vBq_z8w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'This was a quite unique experience, I’ve had one of the best pastas ever here. You feel the history and pride of this place when you step in, fully crowded with tourists and locals alike, my taste buds just connected here from everything, starting from the salad and appetizers to the deserts and espresso. Must stop if you are in bologna.', 'time': 1726005569, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Andrea Perez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105058561096904617120/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVxefmTgntJFeWHU1tcZ9g6z-QdD7bansTy6e722MBA9NfEnktn=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'We loved this place, so much that we went twice while we were in Bologna for a little holiday. The service was excellent -Tomas was lovely. The food is super tasty and everything is reasonably priced. We basically tried everything on the menu (besides desserts) and there wasn’t anything we didn’t like. A must go!!', 'time': 1729265740, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'A K', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102365514797527658152/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLS5pC554YAMUdjxDxb7ppPei7nb3sKAiEYN3_phf1M53_wRnGv=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': 'We had dinner here and it was an organized mess to have your name down to wait for a table. My commendations to the guy at the door who handled it as good as I’ve seen.

However, food here is just frankly massively overrated. Antipasti was alright, but the pasta was a massive disappointment. It’s basically prepared like a pasta as fast food place. Unless you have been eating at tourist traps, the difference in quality is very evident. We had Tortellini in brodo: there was very little filling, which is supposed to be a harmony of meat and cheese. The pasta sheet was definitely not thin enough before it is hand wrapped. The brodo is also a touch too salty, and tasted like processed chicken soup. Ravioli stuffed with cheese had pieces clumped together which means they either didn’t toss in the pan properly, or it was microwaved. Perhaps we ate on an off day for the kitchen, but the preparation of the tortellini speaks for itself.', 'time': 1730444574, 'translated': False}]

reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Joy H.', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100056498436330269883/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYCaT_l1NYqbUt905C-z6Im3kZSSMJa-ZT2F_GJ3AhJ5YvFmruGQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': '“Fun” “Good Deals” “Food&Drinks Available”

A little piece of haven in the concrete jungle of São Paulo. I appreciate the wide variety of seasonal cut flowers, plants, trees, vases, and garden supplies. The prices are mostly fair and much cheaper than what you find in independent stores outside. The trip is always worth it and I always accidentally bring more plants home than intended. The space is pretty big and can take up hours of time if you’re looking for something specific. reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Ahmad', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112452641218281997194/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIlKa7or-Wj3YTOqQ1rBB0Aux0b42h0_cpsdwl7yvzEQYoiSsM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': "I chose this hotel for a layover stay, and it proved to be a mixed experience. The property itself is quite appealing, boasting a unique character that sets it apart from standard airport hotels.

The highlight of my brief stay was undoubtedly the breakfast. The restaurant exceeded my expectations with its outstanding cuisine and impeccable service. It was a delightful surprise that made my short visit memorable.

However, the hotel's location leaves something to be desired. The surrounding area feels less than inviting, which might be a concern for guests planning a longer stay or hoping to explore the vicinity. The lack of comfort in the immediate neighborhood is a notable drawback.

In summary, while the hotel itself offers charm and excellent dining, its location might not suit all travelers. It's an ideal choice for short layovers where you can enjoy the hotel's amenities without venturing into the surrounding area.", 'time': 1729202690, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Sara Anderson', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111870026977140183255/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW7VtBf3w9cqGGtvB9rOx_uXJkivNTeFosnMLAyGx_MCNQtg68=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'I have had the pleasure of staying at this property multiple times, and it remains my absolute favorite place to stay in Brooklyn. The location and views are unbeatable – truly the best in the city. But what sets this place apart is the incredible staff.
